We requested a burger with bacon and no Cheese, but they didn’t add the bacon and did put cheese. The description of the fries says “seasoned to perfection,” there wasn’t even salt on them. The onion rings had no breading, were covered in grease so arrived in a soggy pile. This place is a Medford staple and one of the few places left in Medford where you can get an old Boston style roast beef sandwich with sauce.  My favorite menu item is the haddock sub with tarter, ketchup and pickles.  My mom gets the seafood platter for its fried clams.  The place has the best coleslaw hands down especially if you do not like a lot of mayo.  I wish they would go back to the smaller sized haddock pieces which stayed crispy longer than the big ones.  Also I wish they would go back to smaller fries rather than the steak fries.  These are just my preferences. Nothing fancy here, just low priced, suprisingly good comfort food.
